gomodel:SYNGO_3025  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" , "Rationale: Fig.4: \"Electron micrographs of the cerebellar cortex showing immunoreactivity for SK2 during postnatal development as detected using a pre-embedding immunogold method.\"\n- \"At P21, the highest density of SK2 immunoparticles was detected along the extrasynaptic plasma membrane of PC dendritic spines, followed by dendritic shafts (Figures 4K-L; Table Table1).1). At the presynaptic level, immunolabelling for SK2 was identifiable in PF synapses and their terminals (Figures 4M-N; Table Table1).1).\"\n\n27/3/2018 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: - \"OF-1 mice from the day of birth (P0) to adulthood obtained from the Animal H...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
